title: All of Trump's Whitehouse demolitions, reconstructions and changes
description: US President Donald Trump is slowly changing the iconic Whitehouse building.  First, Trump raised two flags in June on the North and the South Lawns.  In July, on the orders of the president, the rose garden was removed and paved over with Indiana limestone.  The colonnade has now been made into the Presidential Walk of Fame, representing all the presidents other than Biden, who has been replaced with an autopen.  The Oval Office has also undergone an unrecognisable makeover.  Finally, the East Wing was demolished over the summer to create room for a massively out-of-proportioned ballroom.

title: The body of a 25-year-old woman was swept ashore at Maroubra Beach
description: A 25-year-old woman's body was found in Sydney's eastern suburbs after being swept out to sea by a wave at Maroubra Beach.   New South Wales police reported that she was knocked into a tidal rock pool before drowning.   Her identity has not been released.

title: Search underway for missing swimmer in Coogee
description: A man in his 20s has reportedly vanished in the water in Coogee, raising concerns about his safety.

title: Dubai’s incredible fireworks display off the Burj Khalifa
description: Dubai put on a spectacular fireworks display, ushering in the beginning of 2026.  The centrepiece of the fireworks display was the Burj Khalifa, which is the world's tallest skyscraper.

title: Search for missing 14-year-old after boat capsizes in Sydney
description: A 14-year-old boy is missing after his boat capsized at Palm Beach, Sydney, where emergency services responded quickly to the incident.   One man was recovered but unfortunately died, while another was rescued by helicopter.   Large surf and bad weather are complicating ongoing search efforts.

title: Two New Year's Eve stabbings in Melbourne
description: Police are looking for a group of people allegedly responsible for two stabbings.   It was just before midnight on New Year's Eve when two stabbings took place on Lygon Street in Melbourne’s North.  Two men with stab wounds were taken to the hospital with serious injuries.   Police are still on the hunt for those allegedly responsible.

title: Surf Lifesaving program for seniors hopes to decrease coastal drownings
description: Surf Lifesaving Australia is calling on older Australians to get involved with the Silver Salty’s program.  The National initiative is designed to get older Australians engaged with their local clubs and stay active, connected and confident around the water.  Last year, 154 lives lost to drowning on Australia’s coast occurred outside of the surf lifesaving flags, or at unpatrolled locations and outside of patrol times.  More than half of coastal drownings are Australians aged 55 years or older.  It’s hoped programs like this can help keep seniors engaged and more involved.

title: Athens' beautiful NYE firework display lit up the city
description: Athens marks the beginning of the new year with an explosive firework display.   Fireworks could be seen across the city with the main cluster coming out of the Greek monument, The Pantheon.

title: Russia release video of a supposed Ukrainian drone
description: Russia's defence ministry released footage of a drone that was allegedly involved in an attack on Putin's residence.  Russia claims it was among 91 drones launched by Ukraine.   Ukraine has denied the accusation, accusing Moscow of sabotaging peace talks.

title: ‘A terrible start’: Australians warned to be careful after a series of incidents kicked of 2026
description: New South Wales Shadow Police Minister Paul Toole highlights the dangers on waterways and roads as the New Year begins, following multiple tragic incidents already this year.  “If you’re going to be out there on our waterways, make sure that you are doing the right thing,” Mr Toole said.  “A terrible start for many families today to hear of those tragic incidents that have already occurred.  “At the end of the day, it’s about keeping yourself safe.”

title: Thousands gather to watch Qatar’s Lusail Boulevard showered in dazzling fireworks
description: Qatar rings in the New Year with a fireworks display accompanied by a dance version of Coldplay's ‘Sky Full of Stars’.  The firework display took place in and around Qatar's Lusail Boulevard.  Thousands gathered to watch the captivating display.

title: ‘Digging his head in the sand’: Albanese slammed for not holding a Royal Commission
description: New South Wales Shadow Police Minister Paul Toole slams Prime Minister Anthony Albanese for not holding a Royal Commission despite the public outcry.   The Bondi tragedy has prompted over 100 calls for a Royal Commission to investigate how those on watch lists can access firearms.  “The people of Australia are calling for a royal commission,” Mr Toole told Sky News Australia.  “How does someone that’s on a watchlist even get a firearm.  “There are many questions that need to be answered here.  “You’ve got the Prime Minister Anthony Albanese, who's digging his head in the sand and basically saying we’re not going to have one.”

title: London welcomes the New Year in spectacular style
description: London rang in the New Year with a dazzling fireworks display launched from the London Eye.  Set to a high-energy soundtrack celebrating British music, the show played out in front of tens of thousands of spectators lining the river.   Further north, Scotland marked the occasion with Edinburgh’s famous Hogmanay Street party.   Tens of thousands packed the city centre, dancing to welcome the year ahead.

title: Emergency bushfire warning in Perth
description: A bushfire near Perth Airport has prompted an emergency warning for Maida Vale, Kalamunda, and Forrestfield, affecting 800 homes and businesses.  155 firefighters are currently on the ground battling the flames.  While the blaze is contained, it is not yet controlled.  There has been no damage to property reported.

title: Trump arrives at Mar-a-Lago for NYE celebrations
description: US President Donald Trump and the US First Lady Melania Trump arrive for the New Year's Eve celebrations at Mar-a-Lago. ​ The event is a hotspot for Republican figures, MAGA elite, and the president’s allies. ​ The guest list has not been disclosed.
